{{Top|canon=Dark Trooper project}}
{{Quote|What I unveil today will mark a new era for the Empire. We will be able to decimate the Rebels just as we did the Jedi Knights. At last the Emperor's war will be filled only with the glory and beauty of decisive victory.|[[Rom Mohc]]|audio=DecisiveVictory-DF.flac|<ref name="Star Wars: Dark Forces">''[[Star Wars: Dark Forces]]''</ref>}}
[[File:Dark_Troopers.jpg|thumb|300px|The three phases of Dark Troopers]]
The '''Dark Trooper Project''' was a program run by [[General/Legends|General]] [[Rom Mohc]] of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], funded by [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Palpatine/Legends|Palpatine]], to develop what would have become next generation [[Stormtrooper/Legends|stormtroopers]]/[[Battle droid/Legends|battle droids]], the [[Dark Trooper/Legends|dark troopers]].

The factory ship ''[[Arc Hammer]]'' served as the main production facility of the battle droids.

==History==
===Dark Trooper Phase Zero Project===
The [[Phase Zero dark trooper|Dark Trooper Phase Zero]] project was implemented in the early years of the Empire to deal with a shortage of experienced troops. To return veterans of the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] to peak condition, their limbs and organs were removed and replaced with [[Cybernetics/Legends|cybernetics]] using much of the same technology used to transform [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] into a cyborg. In some cases, over 70% of a clone's body was replaced. With their years of combat experience and cybernetic enhancements, the units that did make it onto the field were undeniably effective. However, as the subjects were forcibly recruited into the project, many Phase Zero Dark Troopers could not cope with the state of being more machine than man and attempted suicide. The project was eventually shut down as the Empire grew in power and the recruitment rate of non-clones rose.

===Development===
The Dark Trooper Project was the brainchild of General Rom Mohc who drew from his experiences helping [[Tagge Company/Legends|TaggeCo]] develop the [[Z-X3 experimental droid trooper]], as well as the Dark Trooper Phase Zero Project he oversaw in the earlier years of the Empire. General Mohc, working with the [[Imperial Department of Military Research/Legends|Imperial Department of Military Research]], requisitioned the ''Arc Hammer'' to both construct, house, and transport his new little army. However, not everyone in the Empire supported the project. Several officers and politicians had reservations about droids dating from the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]] experiences. Notably [[Grand Vizier/Legends|Grand Vizier]] [[Sate Pestage/Legends|Sate Pestage]] never thought the project would work.

[[File:Dark_Trooper.jpg|thumb|right|150px|A dark trooper attacks a rebel base.]]
The project was divided into three phases: phases [[Phase I Dark Trooper|I]], [[Phase II Dark Trooper/Legends|II]], and [[Phase III Dark Trooper|III]]. While the Phase I dark troopers were little more than skeletal prototypes they were put into some use early on by General Rom Mohc guarding installations. A peculiarity of the Phase I when compared to the later stages is that instead of a blaster rifle, or some other projectile weapon, it was equipped with a retractable vibrosword and a blast shield.

===Deployment===
{{Quote|Dark trooper: release.|[[Rom Mohc]]|audio=DarkTrooperRelease-DF.flac|<ref name="Star Wars: Dark Forces" />}}
Success for the project was ultimately achieved with Phase II. After initial production of the Phase II dark troopers, an [[Attack on Tak Base|attack]] was launched on [[Talay/Legends|Talay]] [[Tak Base]]. The attack proved the capabilities of Phase II dark troopers; the base was completely wiped out in minutes. These battle droids were larger, bulkier, and equipped with armor of similar design to that of stormtroopers. This armor was made of [[Phrik/Legends|phrik]], a dense and durable alloy that was difficult for even lightsabers to cut through. The Phase II carried a weapon capable of firing both plasma shells and explosive rockets.

Not content with the modest success of the Phase II, Rom Mohc went on to develop the Phase III, intended as the final goal of the Dark Trooper project. To General Mohc, the Phase III Dark Trooper would represent the ultimate Imperial battlefield infantry, also serving as a highly advanced power armor exosuit for living soldiers. Only one prototype was ever constructed of this most devastating of the Dark Troopers. General Mohc himself donned this armor to defend the ''Arc Hammer'' from [[Kyle Katarn]], who had boarded the massive factory ship on a mission to destroy it and end the project.

===Failure===
{{Quote|I ''told'' you it would never work.|[[Sate Pestage/Legends|Sate Pestage]]|<ref name="The New Essential Guide to Droids">''[[The New Essential Guide to Droids]]''</ref>}}
Under orders from [[Mon Mothma/Legends|Mon Mothma]], Kyle Katarn and [[Jan Ors]] continually sabotaged the production facilities. Kyle Katarn quickly infilitrated and sabotaged a number of key facilities including the phrik [[Gromas Mines|mines]] on [[Gromas 16]] and the phrik refining facility and Phase II factory on [[Anteevy/Legends|Anteevy]]. Eventually the mercenary infiltrated the ''Arc Hammer'', where Mohc and Katarn had their final showdown in single combat. Mohc was killed in battle, and the ''Arc Hammer'' was destroyed by sequencer charges placed in precisely chosen key locations within the ship.

Furious at the time and credits wasted on the project, Palpatine ended all production of the Dark Troopers and even went so far as to withdraw funding for all Imperial battle droids being developed at that time. Despite the failure of the project and the loss of Mohc, Vader maintained several remaining Dark Trooper prototype suits, and used them as guards for [[Bast Castle|his castle]] on [[Vjun/Legends|Vjun]].

==Behind the scenes==
The Dark Trooper Project is the main background scenario and objective of the [[Star Wars video games|video game]] ''[[Star Wars: Dark Forces]]''.

In the game, Rom Mohc is the only figure seen behind the Project. According to early drafts versions of the scenario, eventually cut from the final game, another figure would be [[Ruu San]], a [[Imperial Special Operations|Special Operations]] agent, entailed with protecting the secrecy of the project during its production.<ref name="Revving Up">{{GalaxyCite|1|Game Room|Game Room: Revving Up the 'Jedi Engine'}}</ref>

